Key Match Events: Diamondbacks outfielder Corbin Carroll hit an inside-the-park home run in the first inning.
Los Angeles' Shohei Ohtani, Mookie Betts, and Freddie Freeman hit back-to-back-to-back home runs in the first inning.
The Dodgers took an 8-6 lead in the ninth inning and held on for the win.
Post-Match Reflections: Arizona manager Torey Lovullo said, 'There was a lot of excitement in this building. I felt the energy. The fans were engaged. There were a lot of fireworks for the first two innings. … It felt like we did enough to stay in this game.'
Josh Bell said it felt like a postseason atmosphere.
Miscellaneous Highlights: For only the second time in franchise history, the Arizona Diamondbacks drew more than 50,000 fans for a regular season game Saturday against the Los Angeles Dodgers.
Saturday’s announced attendance was 50,041, the second-largest regular season crowd at Chase Field.
